abstract: Police waged an hours-long gunfight with two men armed with high-powered rifles on Tuesday in and around a New Jersey cemetery and kosher market, leaving six people dead, including one officer and both suspects, authorities said.
snippet: Police waged an hours-long gunfight with two men armed with high-powered rifles on Tuesday in and around a New Jersey cemetery and kosher market, leaving six people dead, including one officer and both suspects, authorities said.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Police waged an hours-long gunfight with two men armed with high-powered rifles on Tuesday in and around a New Jersey cemetery and kosher market, leaving six people dead, including one officer and both suspects, authorities said.
headline_main: New Jersey Gun Battle Leaves Six Dead, Including Cop and Both Suspects
headline_print_headline: New Jersey Gun Battle Leaves Six Dead, Including Cop and Both Suspects

abstract: While many American officials are eager to avoid the new tariffs, the president could go either way.
snippet: While many American officials are eager to avoid the new tariffs, the president could go either way.
lead_paragraph: New tariffs on over $100 billion of Chinese goods are due to take effect on Sunday, but the Trump administration is sending mixed signals on delaying them as the United States and China keep haggling over a trade deal.

abstract: Pretrial proceedings revealed the couple’s $230,000 monthly spending, which enabled $12,000 splurges for cigars and $7,000 for fountain pens.

lead_paragraph: The acrimonious divorce case of Rudolph W. Giuliani and his estranged wife, Judith, a battle that had played out in court and across tabloid headlines for more than a year and a half, came to an abrupt — and harmonious — end on Tuesday evening, according to her lawyer.

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump, in a meeting with Russian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov on Tuesday, warned Russia not to interfere in U.S. elections, the White House said.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump, in a meeting with Russian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov on Tuesday, warned Russia not to interfere in U.S. elections, the White House said.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. President Donald Trump, in a meeting with Russian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov on Tuesday, warned Russia not to interfere in U.S. elections, the White House said.
headline_main: Trump Warned Russia Not to Interfere in U.S. Elections: White House
headline_print_headline: Trump Warned Russia Not to Interfere in U.S. Elections: White House

abstract: Documents reveal that American leaders, civilian and military, misled the public about the prospects of success there.
snippet: Documents reveal that American leaders, civilian and military, misled the public about the prospects of success there.
lead_paragraph: What emerges from a tranche of documents, obtained by The Washington Post, outlining the abject failure of the war in Afghanistan and the decades of lies told about it, is the inescapable notion that the American government refuses to be honest with itself.

abstract: Facing intense pressure to answer questions about his work in the private sector, Democratic presidential contender Pete Buttigieg on Tuesday disclosed a roster of former consulting clients that include a major health insurance provider, a nationwide electronics retailer, the U.S. Department of Energy and the Department of Defense.
snippet: Facing intense pressure to answer questions about his work in the private sector, Democratic presidential contender Pete Buttigieg on Tuesday disclosed a roster of former consulting clients that include a major health insurance provider, a nationw...
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Facing intense pressure to answer questions about his work in the private sector, Democratic presidential contender Pete Buttigieg on Tuesday disclosed a roster of former consulting clients that include a major health insurance provider, a nationwide electronics retailer, the U.S. Department of Energy and the Department of Defense.
headline_main: Buttigieg Discloses Ex-Clients as Fundraising Swing Begins
headline_print_headline: Buttigieg Discloses Ex-Clients as Fundraising Swing Begins

abstract: The House should take its own sweet time and investigate many more aspects of the president’s perfidious behavior.
snippet: The House should take its own sweet time and investigate many more aspects of the president’s perfidious behavior.
lead_paragraph: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi was essentially forced into impeachment. Now, after a little less than two months of investigation, she hopes to bring the process to a close. On Tuesday, House Democrats revealed their articles of impeachment against the president. One focuses on abuse of power, the other on obstruction of Congress.
